item.title: MDE Impacts
item.description: Mississippi Department of Education (MDE) District Impact Data Overview # What is “Impact Data”? # This Mississippi Department of Education (MDE) releases impact data each year. After MAAP (Mississippi Academic Assessment Program) testing in April and May, the MDE begins releasing data in June and ends with the final impact data around August or September. 700 Point Impact Data Overview # Here is the 700 point school (elementary and middle schools) impact data template:
